parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become difficult to shift, leading to accidents, injuries, or strandings.
Transmission cooler line failure can cause transmission fluid leakage, leading to overheating, damage to the transmission, and potentially causing accidents or strandings.
Shifter arm failure can cause the vehicle to shift out of gear unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or strandings.
Air conditioner failure can cause discomfort, distraction, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Failure of the air conditioner to operate properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system leaks and odors can cause a fire hazard, especially while driving, and lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Strong fuel smell from the vehicle
fuel fumes coming from the vents
fuel injector pouring fuel into cylinders and dumping it out of exhaust pipes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to honor recall notices can lead to unresolved safety issues, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: Dealer refuses to repair or replace faulty fuel injection system
or other components despite recall notices.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel injection system failure can cause fuel leaks, fires, and accidents.
symptoms: Fuel injector pouring fuel into cylinders and dumping it out of exhaust pipes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rack and pinion steering system can cause loss of power steering, making it difficult to control the vehicle, especially at high speeds, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel shakes or vibrates
the vehicle wanders or drifts while driving
fluid leaks from the steering pump area
the steering wheel becomes loose or has excessive play.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tie rod bushings can cause loss of steering control, making it difficult to control the vehicle, especially at high speeds, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel shakes or vibrates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering pump can cause loss of power steering, making it difficult to control the vehicle, especially at high speeds, which can lead to accidents.
